  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Philippines Measles Outbreak 2019</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">6 February 2019 government declared a measles outbreak. Since January 2019 there have been 16,349 cases of measles reported, with 261 deaths. Almost every region of the Philippines has been affected, the most vulnerable are young children (1-2 years old). 12 February 2019 IFRC activated a 5 month DREF for CHF 181,417 to support PRC in two main ways: providing vaccinations to 60,000 children&#xC2;&#xA0;and a nationwide education campaign on the importance of getting vaccinated. 6 March 2019 Emergency Appeal (CHF 2m) launched to supported the vaccination of a further 200,000 children and one million to be reached with health information. Appeal to run from April - September 2019.</narrative>
  </description>
